President Obama has declared a major disaster in Mississippi and ordered federal aid to assist with recovery efforts after Hurricane Isaac. Federal funding will be available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures in various counties. Terry L. Quarles has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. More counties and forms of assistance may be added after the Preliminary Damage Assessments are completed. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.